quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  9,123,"O ye who believe! fight the unbelievers who gird you about, and let them find firmness in you: and know that God is with those who fear Him"
  9,124,"Whenever there cometh down a sura, some of them say: \"Which of you has had His faith increased by it?\" Yea, those who believe,- their faith is increased and they do rejoice"
  9,125,"But those in whose hearts is a disease,- it will add doubt to their doubt, and they will die in a state of Unbelief"
  9,126,"See they not that they are tried every year once or twice? Yet they turn not in repentance, and they take no heed"
  9,127,"Whenever there cometh down a Sura, they look at each other, (saying), \"Doth anyone see you?\" Then they turn aside: God hath turned their hearts (from the light); for they are a people that understand not"
  9,128,"Now hath come unto you an Apostle from amongst yourselves: it grieves him that ye should perish: ardently anxious is he over you: to the Believers is he most kind and merciful"
  9,129,"But if they turn away, Say: \"God sufficeth me: there is no god but He: On Him is my trust,- He the Lord of the Throne (of Glory) Supreme"